{
  "texts": [
    "In §4.2, we demonstrated that Unknown fine-tuning examples increase the risk of overfitting.",
    "We now observe that this also applies to WeaklyKnown, though to a lesser degree.",
    "Specifically, at CONVERGENCE, D WeaklyKnown and D Unknown experience significant performance drops compared to EARLY_STOP (39.2 → 35.4 and 37.5 → 25.8).",
    "With training to CONVERGENCE, they show a mod-est improvement on WeaklyKnown and Unknown but substantially degrade on HighlyKnown and MaybeKnown.",
    "This highlights that the decrease in performance is strongly attributed to an increased rate of hallucinations w.r.t."
  ]
}